Module stincmale.idenator
Package stincmale.idenator

Class AbstractTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • stincmale.idenator.AbstractTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LongIdGenerator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConcurrentTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator, OptimisticTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator1, OptimisticTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator2, OptimisticTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator3, StampedTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator1, StampedTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator2, SynchronizedTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator1, SynchronizedTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator2
    @ThreadSafe
public abstract class AbstractTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator
extends Object
implements LongIdGenerator
    This ID generator can be represented as an optimization around another ID generator (specifically hiGenerator), which require noticeable amount of resources (usually time) to produce a new identifier (e.g. because it requires accessing a persistent storage to generate a new identifier).

    This ID generator maintains two values: hi and lo, and uses them for calculation of a new identifier. Hi values are identifiers themselves, usually take significant time to be generated and virtually unbounded. Lo values are usually cheap to produce, bounded by loUpperBoundOpen, must be unique only within the same hi value.

    This ID generator can work in two modes: Hi/Lo and pooled.

    Hi/Lo mode
    This mode is suitable to wrap any hiGenerator, but the downside is that AbstractTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator working in this mode is not compatible (see stincmale.idenator) with the wrapped hiGenerator. See calculateId(long, long) for the formula which is used to calculate identifiers in this mode.

    This mode is analogous to HiLoOptimizer in Hibernate ORM, and is also described here.

    Pooled mode (recommended)
    This mode is preferable to Hi/Lo, because AbstractTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator working in this mode is compatible with the wrapped hiGenerator. However, this mode requires hiGenerator to be sparse (see stincmale.idenator).

    This mode is analogous to PooledLoOptimizer in Hibernate ORM, and is also described here.

    Flavours (see stincmale.idenator):

    • This ID generator is persistent if hiGenerator is persistent and the same getLoUpperBoundOpen is used in different executions of the program.
    • This ID generator is strictly increasing if hiGenerator is strictly increasing, otherwise this ID generator is nonmonotonic.
    This class is thread-safe, but does not impose this restriction on its subclasses.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator

        protected AbstractTwoPhaseLongIdGenerator​(LongIdGenerator hiGenerator,
                                          long loUpperBoundOpen,
                                          boolean pooled)
        Parameters:
        hiGenerator - A hi value generator (the ID generator which we are optimizing). hiGenerator is allowed to be not thread-safe.
        loUpperBoundOpen - This parameter specifies how many identifiers we can generate after obtaining a new hi value without retrieving another hi value again. Must be positive. lo ∈ [0; loUpperBoundOpen).

        If persistent behaviour (see stincmale.idenator) is required, then this parameter should be the same for different executions of the program. Using different values in different executions can sometimes be possible, but this is beyond of scope of this documentation.

        pooled - Defines whether this ID generator will work in Hi/Lo or in pooled (recommended) mode (this affects behaviour of calculateId(long, long)).

        If hiGenerator is sparse (see stincmale.idenator), then specify true and specify (sparseness + 1) as loUpperBoundOpen. Otherwise, or if you don't know anything about the behaviour of hiGenerator, specify false.

        For the sake of testing, specifying pooled true and loUpperBoundOpen 1 is allowed, despite it means that sparseness is 0, which is not allowed by the definition of sparseness. But we may think that an ID generator with 0 sparseness is a degenerate case of a sparse ID generator.

    • Method Detail

      • calculateId

        protected final long calculateId​(long hi,
                                 long lo)
        Calculates an identifier as hi + lo if this ID generator isPooled(), otherwise as hi * loUpperBoundOpen + lo.

        Pooled and not pooled (we will be calling it Hi/Lo) ID generators are simpler to explain with the assumption that hiGenerator is strictly increasing (see stincmale.idenator).

        Parameters:
        hi - A hi value. Must not be equal to UNINITIALIZED.
        lo - A lo value. lo ∈ [0; loUpperBoundOpen).
        Returns:
        The identifier uniquely defined by the supplied hi, lo and numberOfIdsPerHi values.
